<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="884" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/157: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Special Mission at Lausanne</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-20T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 20,
                                        1922—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>3. Your telegram no. 1 of November 19. There is no objection to your
                            having informal preliminary conversations, at your discretion, <pb facs="1166" n="1042" xml:id="pg_1042"/> with Turks or any others.
                            You should, of course, keep in mind that you are not authorized to make
                            any commitments except on instructions from the Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>